column5: Pst week has been great for getting out on some of the local ice. Heck, even the fish were playing nice for a couple of days. Regretably the high cell stalled the bite the past 2 days but the weather was too beautiful to pass up. Tuesday's volunteers.  Rob  d"s squeze showing him how it is done  A couple of the  local thugs    Now if only the ice at the smelt grounds would firm up.
Looks good!!!  I'd love to go for some smelt through the ice....I heard they were in pretty thick by Fishmaster's last week....but I don't think the ice is holding up too well down there right now...
It was a slow day out there yesterday Bruce and wouldn't ya know it, my gf caught more perch than a few of us, lol.
Do the smelt still come into Ramey's Bend?
I believe there is good numbers of smelt at Ramey's Bend every Winter, Rick.
They were there last year...would basically bite an empty hook!
Great report and pics Bruce Nice bunch of guests Thanks for sharing Jacques
How do you like Michelle's Lady Gaga pose?
I was waiting for you to post some pictures of that day.
There wasn't much action to  take pics of     The fish were kinda camera shy
